[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":542},["ShallowReactive",2],{"docs-/news/articles/2022-06-14-bootstrapping-cellular-networks":3,"navigation":117},{"_path":4,"_dir":5,"_draft":6,"_partial":6,"_locale":7,"title":8,"description":9,"layout":5,"urlImage":10,"imageBackground":7,"subtitle":11,"rightLabel":12,"leftLabel":13,"cardID":14,"tags":15,"excerpt":18,"body":37,"_type":112,"_id":113,"_source":114,"_file":115,"_extension":116},"/news/articles/2022-06-14-bootstrapping-cellular-networks","articles",false,"","LwM2M, Bootstrapping in Cellular Networks","OMASpecWorks announces the creation of a new Work Item, LwM2M Device Bootstrapping in Cellular Networks The Lightweight M2M protocol (LwM2M) has proven itself to be well suited to operating within Cellular networks, supporting a wide range of Device Types from Low Latency critical IoT applications (e.g., remote performance monitoring) to high latency massive IoT applications (e.g., water metering).","/images/news/bootstrapping.jpeg","New Work Item","OMA SpecWorks","2022-Jun-14",14,[16,17],"bootstrap","cellular networks",{"type":19,"children":20},"root",[21],{"type":22,"tag":23,"props":24,"children":25},"element","p",{},[26,29,35],{"type":27,"value":28},"text","OMASpecWorks announces the creation of a new Work Item, ",{"type":22,"tag":30,"props":31,"children":32},"strong",{},[33],{"type":27,"value":34},"LwM2M Device Bootstrapping in Cellular Networks",{"type":27,"value":36}," The Lightweight M2M protocol (LwM2M) has proven itself to be well suited to operating within Cellular networks, supporting a wide range of Device Types from Low Latency critical IoT applications (e.g., remote performance monitoring) to high latency massive IoT applications (e.g., water metering).",{"type":19,"children":38,"toc":106},[39,48,53,58,65,79,85],{"type":22,"tag":23,"props":40,"children":41},{},[42,43,47],{"type":27,"value":28},{"type":22,"tag":30,"props":44,"children":45},{},[46],{"type":27,"value":34},{"type":27,"value":36},{"type":22,"tag":23,"props":49,"children":50},{},[51],{"type":27,"value":52},"There are currently multiple methods for cellular device management, but in most cases, the devices somehow must be provisioned to a LwM2M server before use. At a minimum this is the URL address of the LwM2M server, but it often also includes security credentials for that particular LwM2M server. Provisioning this information is done within the supply chain and adds cost and complexity to the roll out of device.",{"type":22,"tag":23,"props":54,"children":55},{},[56],{"type":27,"value":57},"This work item is focused on avoiding supply chain complexity in cellular networks by utilising their inherent trustworthiness and security. Cellular networks already provide root of trust anchoring to the cellular subscription, various levels of encryption on the radio network, and a secure domain for which access can be controlled.  The goal is to enable a manufacturer to create devices in an entirely generic way and use a cellular subscription that allow the devices to automatically attach to any operator defined server.",{"type":22,"tag":59,"props":60,"children":62},"h3",{"id":61},"about-open-mobile-alliance",[63],{"type":27,"value":64},"About Open Mobile Alliance",{"type":22,"tag":23,"props":66,"children":67},{},[68,70],{"type":27,"value":69},"OMA is the leading industry forum for developing market-driven, interoperable mobile service enablers. OMA was formed by the world’s leading mobile operators, device and network suppliers, information technology companies, and content providers as the industry focal point for the development of mobile service enabler specifications. OMA is a non-profit organization that delivers open specifications supporting the billions of new and existing terminals operating across traditional cellular operator networks and emerging networks supporting machine-to-machine communications for the Internet of Things (IoT). New work in OMA is leading to the development of next-generation mobile services in areas such as Device Management, LBS, IoT, APIs and more. See ",{"type":22,"tag":71,"props":72,"children":76},"a",{"href":73,"rel":74},"https://omaspecworks.org/about/",[75],"nofollow",[77],{"type":27,"value":78},"About OMA",{"type":22,"tag":59,"props":80,"children":82},{"id":81},"about-lightweightm2m-lwm2m",[83],{"type":27,"value":84},"About LightweightM2M (LwM2M)",{"type":22,"tag":23,"props":86,"children":87},{},[88,90,97,99],{"type":27,"value":89},"Please use this link to download ",{"type":22,"tag":71,"props":91,"children":94},{"href":92,"rel":93},"https://www.openmobilealliance.org/release/LightweightM2M/Lightweight_Machine_to_Machine-v1_1-OMASpecworks.pdf",[75],[95],{"type":27,"value":96},"LwM2M v1.1",{"type":27,"value":98},", ",{"type":22,"tag":71,"props":100,"children":103},{"href":101,"rel":102},"https://www.openmobilealliance.org/release/LightweightM2M/",[75],[104],{"type":27,"value":105},"LwM2M v1.2",{"title":7,"searchDepth":107,"depth":107,"links":108},2,[109,111],{"id":61,"depth":110,"text":64},3,{"id":81,"depth":110,"text":84},"markdown","content:5.news:articles:2022-06-14-bootstrapping-cellular-networks.md","content","5.news/articles/2022-06-14-bootstrapping-cellular-networks.md","md",[118,217,259,335,366,431,445,466,535,537,539],{"title":119,"_path":120,"children":121},"OMASPECWORKS","/omaspecworks",[122,136,150,203,215],{"title":123,"_path":124,"children":125},"About","/omaspecworks/about",[126,128,131,134],{"title":12,"_path":127},"/omaspecworks/about/omaspecworks",{"title":129,"_path":130},"Intellectual Property Rights","/omaspecworks/about/ipr",{"title":132,"_path":133},"Policies & Terms","/omaspecworks/about/policies-terms",{"title":135,"_path":124},"About OMA SpecWorks",{"title":137,"_path":138,"children":139},"Membership","/omaspecworks/membership",[140,143,146,149],{"title":141,"_path":142},"Benefits","/omaspecworks/membership/benefits",{"title":144,"_path":145},"Join OMA","/omaspecworks/membership/join",{"title":147,"_path":148},"Membe